ents-via-app-126011000505_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fphonepe-launches-pg-bolt-to-secure-visa-mastercard-payments-via-app-126011000505_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fphonepe-launches-pg-bolt-to-secure-visa-mastercard-payments-via-app-126011000505_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20run%20our%20bakery%20out%20of%20shipping%20containers.%20It%20was%20an%20unexpectedly%20cost-effective%20solution%20to%20scaling%20our%20business.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20posing%20outside%20of%20a%20shipping%20container.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695ec5fb04eda4732f2eaacf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChrissy%20and%20Ben%20Salif%20Traore%20began%20using%20shipping%20containers%20as%20their%20business%20expanded.%3Cp%3ENina%20Roberts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChrissy%20Traore%20and%20her%20husband%20started%20a%20bakery%20in%20Upstate%20New%20York%20after%20leaving%20the%20city.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20they%20ran%20out%20of%20space%20as%20business%20boomed%20Traore%20started%20utilizing%20shipping%20containers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShipping%20containers%20provided%20a%20quick%20solution%20and%20ended%20up%20being%20cost-effective.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Chrissy%20Traore%2C%2041%2C%20who%20opened%20See%20%26amp%3B%20Be%20Kitchen%20with%20her%20husband%20Ben%20Salif%20Traore%20in%20Cairo%2C%20New%20York%2C%20about%2040%20miles%20from%20Albany%2C%20New%20York.%20When%20their%20business%20expanded%20quickly%2C%20they%20began%20running%20parts%20of%20it%20out%20of%20shipping%20containers%20on%20their%20property.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20and%20I%20met%20while%20I%20was%20a%20chef%20and%20he%20was%20a%20baker.%20We%20worked%20at%20the%20same%20restaurant%20%E2%80%94%20they%20had%20a%20bakery%20and%20a%20restaurant%20right%20next%20door%2C%20and%20I%20was%20their%20pizza%20chef%20and%20he%20was%20their%20head%20baker.%20I%20had%20to%20mix%20my%20pizza%20dough%20in%20his%20mixer%20and%20that's%20kind%20of%20how%20we%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20Madison%20Avenue%20in%20marketing%20and%20brand%20strategy%2C%20and%20in%202008%2C%20the%20economy%20crashed%20and%20my%20job%20crashed%20too.%20When%20that%20happened%2C%20I%20moved%20into%20food.%20I%20took%20a%20job%20on%20an%20ice%20cream%20truck%20and%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-change-food-influencer-family-support-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efell%20in%20love%20with%20food%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20the%20food%20industry%20in%20various%20ways%20in%20New%20York%20City%20from%20about%202008%20until%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20I%20was%20unhappy%20with%20the%20way%20that%20they%20treated%20employees.%20I%20was%20in%20management%20at%20the%20time%2C%20so%20I%20could%20see%20the%20full%20round%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20has%20to%20be%20a%20better%20way%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20my%20job%20to%20change%20this%20business%20owner%20or%20this%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20and%20I%20talked%20a%20lot%20about%20it%2C%20and%20we%20were%20going%20upstate%20frequently%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20working%20at%20a%20place%20upstate%20as%20their%20first%20chef.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20really%20move%20upstate.%26quot%3B%20It's%20more%20our%20speed.%20We%20like%20the%20outdoors.%20We%20like%20having%20space.%20The%20quality%20of%20life%20is%20better.%20We%20love%20farming%20and%20being%20close%20to%20what's%20happening%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20literally.%20In%202017%20we%20said%2C%20let's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-charlotte-north-carolina-moved-small-nearby-lake-town-happier-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eget%20out%20of%20the%20city%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20money%2C%20and%20we%20had%20to%20be%20scrappy%20and%20thoughtful%20about%20how%20we%20deployed%20the%20resources%20that%20we%20had%20saved.%20We%20wanted%20a%20place%20where%20we%20could%20live%20and%20work%2C%20so%20we%20wanted%20property%20and%20land%20%E2%80%94%20that%20was%20important%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20a%20property%20in%20Cairo%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20it%20had%20been%20a%20bar%20and%20a%20hotel%2C%20so%20it%20was%20already%20grandfathered%20in%20on%20DOH%2C%20and%20had%20some%20structures%20there.%20We%20have%2011%20acres%2C%20and%20the%20house%20was%20practically%20falling%20apart%2C%20so%20we%20could%20afford%20it.%20We%20paid%20%24189%2C900%2C%20and%20that%20was%20it.%20We%20went%20all%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22340a28af-83d4-49a2-b8f2-d4246125baf1%5C%22%3EOur%20business%20was%20rapidly%20expanding%20and%20we%20needed%20more%20buildings%20fast%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20knew%20we%20wanted%20to%20open%20our%20own%20place%20and%20we%20were%20trying%20to%20discover%20what%20that%20was.%20We%20knew%20it%20would%20involve%20Ben's%20bread%20and%20my%20cooking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20renovating%20the%20property%20and%20doing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmall-farmer-explains-what-it-takes-to-stay-in-business-2014-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efarmers%20markets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20we%20got%20to%20know%20the%20community%20that%20we%20were%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20came%20in%20quietly%2C%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20see%20what's%20already%20here%20and%20get%20to%20know%20people%20before%20we%20just%20bash%20them%20over%20the%20head%20with%20what%20we%20do.%26quot%3B%20Let's%20see%20what%20they%20want%2C%20because%20ultimately%20we're%20entering%20a%20community%20that's%20not%20necessarily%20ours%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20posing%20outside%20of%20shipping%20containers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695ec5fb832e0ef1ead75d21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Traore's%20have%20three%20shipping%20containers%20on%20their%20property.%3Cp%3ENina%20Roberts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20moving%20from%20Bed-Stuy%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20and%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20we%20moved%20out%20was%20we%20saw%20that%20happening.%20People%20were%20moving%20in%20and%20they%20would%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20fix%20this.%20This%20is%20broken.%26quot%3B%20And%20I'm%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20broken%3F%20This%20is%20a%20wonderful%20community.%20Please%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometime%20in%202018%2C%20we%20turned%20into%20See%20%26amp%3B%20Be.%20Then%2C%20from%20there%2C%20we%20really%20got%20some%20traction%20at%20farmers%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20doing%20porch%20pickups%20%E2%80%94%20people%20could%20pick%20up%20their%20orders%20at%20a%20local%20massage%20therapist's%20house%20%E2%80%94%20so%20we%20had%20started%20operating%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20have%20a%20physical%20space%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20still%20building%20out%20the%20cafe%20in%20the%20very%20small%20already%20existing%20structure%20on%20our%20property.%20We%20had%20one%20oven%2C%20with%20one%20proofer%2C%20a%20little%20cooktop%20that%20I%20would%20do%20the%20sandwiches%20on%2C%20and%20a%20coffee%20station%20with%20this%20beautiful%20wooden%20bar%20that%20people%20could%20sit%20at.%20And%20we%20opened%20that%20in%20February%20of%202019.%20Ben%20baked%20everything%3B%20I%20r